ory belongs to the people". [[Alexander Berkman]]. "[[Now and After|What Is Communist Anarchism?]]" [http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1138] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523195452/http://theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Alexander_Berkman__What_Is_Communist_Anarchism_.html|date=23 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Steele|first=David Ramsay|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/From_Marx_to_Mises.html?id=_1K6AAAAIAAJ&source=kp_book_description|title=From Marx to Mises: Post-capitalist Society and the Challenge of Economic Calculation|date=1992|publisher=Open Court|isbn=978-0-87548-449-5|pages=43|language=en|quote=One widespread distinction was that socialism socialised production only while communism socialised production and consumption.}}</ref><ref name="Mayne">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6MkTz6Rq7wUC&q=Communist+anarchism+belives+in+collective+ownership&pg=PA131|title=From Politics Past to Politics Future: An Integrated Analysis of Current and Emergent Paradigms|author-first=Alan James|author-last=Mayne|publisher=[[Greenwood Publishing Group]]|access-date=20 September 2010|isbn=978-0275961510|year=1999|archive-date=27 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210327103934/https://books.google.com/books?id=6MkTz6Rq7wUC&q=Communist+anarchism+belives+in+collective+ownership&pg=PA131|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jeiudz5sBV4C&pg=PA14|page=14|title=Anarchism for Know-It-Alls By Know-It-Alls For Know-It-Alls, For Know-It-Alls|publisher=Filiquarian Publishing, LLC.|year=2008|access-date=20 September 2010|isbn=978-1599862187}}</ref><ref>Fabbri, Luigi. "Anarchism and Communism." Northeastern Anarchist #4. 1922. 13 October 2002. [http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/worldwidemovements/fabbrianarandcom.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/60XT4dCPz?url=http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/worldwidemovements/fabbrianarandcom.html|date=29 July 2011